nent\": \"cartservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Cart service operations impacted: EmptyCart from 2.3s to 36.4s (15.8x), GetCart from 2.0s to 15.8s (7.9x)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Checkout service internal operations affected: ShipOrder from 14.4s to 44.7s (3.1x), GetCart from 8.2s to 16.3s (2.0x)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n1. **ProductCatalogService is the most severely affected** - Response times increased by 16.8x, suggesting potential issues with the underlying TiDB database.\n\n2. **Redis performance degradation** - Both HMSET and HGET operations show 9.6x latency increases, indicating Redis infrastructure problems.\n\n3. **Cascading effects** - The Redis and ProductCatalogService issues are propagating upstream to CartService and CheckoutService.\n\n4. **Multiple frontend instances affected** - All three frontend instances (frontend-0, frontend-1, frontend-2) show similar patterns of increased latency when calling downstream services.\n\nThe root cause appears to be infrastructure-related, potentially affecting both the database layer (TiDB for ProductCatalogService) and cache layer (Redis for CartService).", "report_analysis_findings": {"uuid": "1e36872d-481", "component": "tidb-tikv", "reason": "region_pending spike (164.14% change) causing database latency and cascading effects", "reasoning_trace": [{"step": 1, "action": "LoadMetrics(tidb-tikv)", "observation": "region_pending increased 164.14% from 11018 to 1085"}, {"step": 2, "action": "TraceAnalysis(1e36872d-481)", "observation": "productcatalogservice->tidb calls show 16.8x latency increase"}, {"step": 3, "action": "CheckNodePodMapping()", "observation": "productcatalogservice-2 on aiops-k8s-03 affected"}]}, "report_analysis_completed": true}
